<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 26 at 5:56AM CDT until April 26 at 6:30AM CDT by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 630 AM CDT
FOR CENTRAL FOARD AND SOUTHEASTERN HARDEMAN COUNTIES...
At 556 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 4 miles west of
Crowell, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Half dollar size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
Crowell, Margaret, Thalia, and Copper Breaks State Park.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.25 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.
Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
